metatags.sailthru.excerpt: Few individuals have had as great of an impact on the United States as Congressman and Civil Rights icon John Lewis. Following his death last week at age 80, six days of memorial events, services, and processions will take place in his honor. Official proceedings began on Saturday, July 25 in Troy, Alabama, Lewis's hometown. On Monday and Tuesday, Lewis will become the first Black lawmaker to lie in state in the Capitol Rotunda in Washington, D.C, before he is laid to rest in Atlanta, Georgia. Here you'll find the most powerful photographs from Lewis's memorial proceedings, as mourners around the nation celebrate his legacy.
